Topic: Search Options, Wildcards, Condition Builder, Breadcrumbs

Overview
Explained different ways to search data in ServiceNow, usage of wildcard search conditions, how to build advanced filters using condition builder, saving filters, and how breadcrumbs work to manage applied conditions.
Demonstrated using the Incident table.

Previous Video Recap
– What is a Record
– List View vs Form View
– How to create an Incident record

Search Options in ServiceNow

Global Search
• Available on the ServiceNow home screen
• Works similar to Google search
• Returns matching data under various categories like People, Knowledge, Catalog Items
• Example: Search “mobile” → shows related results across the platform

Table Level Search (Incident List Search)
• Appears near the table name (Incident)
• Can search records using fields such as:

Number

Opened date

Short Description

Caller

Priority

State
• Example: Copy incident number → paste in search → shows direct match

Filter Panel Search
• Available inside the filter/condition builder
• Used for structured filtering of records by selecting fields and operators

Cell Based Search
• Search directly under column cells
• Usually used for applying wildcard search conditions

Wildcard Search Conditions

Contains
*term
Example: *network
Result: Records where Short Description contains “network”

Does Not Contain
!*term
Example: !*network
Result: Records where Short Description does not contain “network”

Exact Match
=term
Example: =new (State field)
Result: Only records having exact state “New”

Not Equal
!=term
Example: !=new
Result: All records where state is not “New”

Starts With
term%
Example: network%
Result: Records where description starts with “network”

Ends With
%term
Result: Records where text ends with that term

Condition Builder (Filter Section)

Allows structured multi-condition filtering.

Steps
• Open Incident list: incident.list
• Enable Filter panel
• Select field → select operator → provide value → Run

Examples

State = Closed
Shows all closed incidents

State is one of Closed, In Progress
Shows incidents matching any of the selected states

State is one of Closed, In Progress
AND Priority = High
Shows high priority incidents that are closed or in progress

State is one of Closed, In Progress
AND Priority = High
AND Created on Last Year
Shows records created last year with the above conditions

State is one of Closed, In Progress
AND Priority = High
AND Created on Last Year
OR Created on This Year
Shows matching records from both last year and current year

Saving Filters

• After building a filter, click Save
• Provide a name (e.g. Daily Report)
• Choose visibility: Only Me / Group / Everyone
• Load filters through List Controls → Filter

Breadcrumbs

Shows active filter conditions in a readable format.

Example
All > State is Closed or In Progress > Priority = 2 > Created On Last Year OR This Year

Breadcrumb Features
• View entire applied filter condition
• Click arrows (>) to remove the next condition section
• Click All to return to full incident list
• Right-click breadcrumb to copy query URL or filter script

Example Usage
– Remove last applied condition
– Quickly reset search
– Copy query for documentation or scripts

Key Points

• Multiple search areas exist in ServiceNow
• Wildcards help to quickly narrow down records
• Condition Builder supports complex filtering
• Filters can be saved and reused
• Breadcrumbs allow easy filter navigation and removal